on 处于被误解的地位","headword":"in a false position"},{"type":"entry","text":"how-do-you-do 尴尬局面","headword":"how-do-you-do"},{"type":"entry","text":"shy away from 羞于；回避","headword":"shy away from"},{"type":"entry","text":"go hot and cold 害臊","headword":"go hot and cold"},{"type":"entry","text":"in one's shell 害羞","headword":"in one's shell"},{"type":"section","text":"Step2 学以致用"}]},{"number":795,"blocks":[{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 1"},{"type":"example","text":"A：Sometimes I feel embarrassed about him. （有时候我会为他感到"},{"type":"text","text":"难堪。）"},{"type":"example","text":"B：Yeah, he is always that rude. （是啊，他总是那么粗鲁。）"},{"type":"section","text":"Conversation 2"},{"type":"example","text":"A：Well... I don't know, Derek.（呃…，我不知道，德雷克。）"},{"type":"example","text":"B：Don't be coy, Charlie. This woman is made for you.（别害羞，查"},{"type":"text","text":"利，这个女人非常适合你。）"}]}]}